DoE Examples

Alexandra Chronopoulou

Randomized Complete Block Design (RCBD)

The Oat Varieties Example

library(faraway)
data(oatvar)

Consider an experiment to compare the yield of 8 different varieties of oats. The growing area was heterogeneous and so was grouped into 5 blocks. Each variety was sown once within each block and the yield}= in grams per 16ft row was recorded.

xtabs(yield~variety + block, oatvar)
##        block
## variety   I  II III  IV   V
##       1 296 357 340 331 348
##       2 402 390 431 340 320
##       3 437 334 426 320 296
##       4 303 319 310 260 242
##       5 469 405 442 487 394
##       6 345 342 358 300 308
##       7 324 339 357 352 220
##       8 488 374 401 338 320
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(yield~ variety, oatvar)
plot(yield~block, oatvar)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
with(oatvar, interaction.plot(variety, block,yield))
with(oatvar, interaction.plot(block, variety,yield))

We fit the additive model:

lmodcrbd <- lm(yield~ block + variety, oatvar)
summary(lmodcrbd )

## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Response: yield
##           Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value    Pr(>F)    
## block      4  33396  8348.9  6.2449  0.001008 ** 
## variety    7  77524 11074.8  8.2839 1.804e-05 ***
## Residuals 28  37433  1336.9                      
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# Check Diagnostics
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
plot(lmodcrbd, which=1:2, caption=NULL)

# Tukey's Additivity Test
varcoefs <- c(0, coef(lmodcrbd)[6:12])
blockcoefs <- c(0,coef(lmodcrbd)[2:5])
ab <- rep(varcoefs, each=5)*rep(blockcoefs, 8)
h <- update(lmodcrbd, .~.+ab)
anova(h)
## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Response: yield
##           Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value    Pr(>F)    
## block      4  33396  8348.9  6.0563  0.001299 ** 
## variety    7  77524 11074.8  8.0337 2.787e-05 ***
## ab         1    213   212.9  0.1544  0.697428    
## Residuals 27  37220  1378.5                      
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# RCBD vs CRD Relative Efficiency
lmcrd <- lm(yield~variety, oatvar)
(summary(lmcrd)$sig /summary(lmodcrbd)$sig)^2
## [1] 1.655617

Latin Squares

Wear on Materials Example

library(faraway)
data(abrasion)
matrix(abrasion$material, 4, 4, byrow=TRUE)
##      [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
## [1,] "C"  "D"  "B"  "A" 
## [2,] "A"  "B"  "D"  "C" 
## [3,] "D"  "C"  "A"  "B" 
## [4,] "B"  "A"  "C"  "D"
library(ggplot2)
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 3.6.2
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
ggplot(abrasion, aes(x=run, y=wear, shape=position, group=material))+geom_point() + geom_line(aes(linetype=material))

ggplot(abrasion, aes(x=position, y=wear, shape=run, group=material))+geom_point() + geom_line(aes(linetype=material))

lmodls <- lm(wear ~ material+run+position, abrasion)
drop1(lmodls, test="F")

Balanced Incomplete Block Design

Rabbit weight gain Example

library(faraway)
data(rabbit)
xtabs(gain~treat+block, rabbit)
##      block
## treat   b1  b10   b2   b3   b4   b5   b6   b7   b8   b9
##     a  0.0 37.3 40.1  0.0 44.9  0.0  0.0 45.2 44.0  0.0
##     b 32.6  0.0 38.1  0.0  0.0  0.0 37.3 40.6  0.0 30.6
##     c 35.2  0.0 40.9 34.6 43.9 40.9  0.0  0.0  0.0  0.0
##     d  0.0 42.3  0.0 37.5  0.0 37.3  0.0 37.9  0.0 27.5
##     e  0.0  0.0  0.0  0.0 40.8 32.0 40.5  0.0 38.5 20.6
##     f 42.2 41.7  0.0 34.3  0.0  0.0 42.8  0.0 51.9  0.0
ggplot(rabbit, aes(x=block, y=gain, shape=treat))+geom_point() + theme(legend.position="top", legend.direction="horizontal")

ggplot(rabbit, aes(x=treat, y=gain))+geom_point(position=position_jitter(width=.1))

lmodbibd <- lm(gain~block+treat, rabbit)
drop1(lmodbibd, test="F")
